---
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="About" description="About UI Gems and its author">
  <div class="prose about">
    <h1>About UI Gems</h1>
    <p>
      UI Gems is a technical writing series exploring the edges of CSS — advanced techniques, experimental specifications, and the patterns that make design systems tick. Every article originates here with interactive demos you can edit in the browser, then gets cross-posted to Medium and LinkedIn.
    </p>
    <p>
      The name comes from a simple idea: CSS is full of small, powerful techniques that deserve more attention than a tweet. Each "gem" is a deep dive into one of those techniques — how it works under the hood, when to reach for it, and what it unlocks.
    </p>

    <h2>About the Author</h2>
    <p>
      I'm Luis — a Senior Frontend Engineer with 10+ years building for the web with deep expertise in CSS architecture, design systems, and modern web standards. I spent 8 years at LinkedIn, where I built token-based design systems, a layout engine, and Figma-to-code tooling that improved delivery speed by 40%. I'm currently at Superhuman working on growth experiments.
    </p>
    <p>
      I care deeply about CSS as a language — not just as a styling tool, but as an expressive system for building interfaces. I've been writing about it since I was teaching computer science at university, and I believe technical writing is one of the most underrated forms of knowledge transfer.
    </p>
    <p>
      When I'm not writing CSS or writing *about* CSS, I'm probably making cocktails at home or arguing about things with a close friend.
    </p>

    <h2>Follow Along</h2>
    <p>
      Find me on <a href="https://medium.com/@projectluis">Medium</a>,
      <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/theluistorres">LinkedIn</a>, and
      <a href="https://github.com/semanticpixel">GitHub</a>. Or subscribe
      via <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: var(--content-width);
  }
</style>
